        <div className="roundBottom roundBottom-top">
          <div className="container serviceContent cooperation pt-5  pb-3">
            <div className="row pt-0">
              <div className="col-md-9">
                <div className=" pr-90">
                  <h2 className="serviceContent_title">
                    What is IT Outsourcing
                  </h2>
                  <p>
                    IT outsourcing is the use of external service providers to
                    manage, deliver and support IT-enabled business processes,
                    services and infrastructure. There are a range of benefits
                    of outsourced IT, and many businesses use a blend of IT
                    outsourcing and internal IT teams. <br /> IT outsourcing
                    provider can help your business by providing fully managed
                    services or co-sourced IT support. Fully managed service
                    refers to an IT outsourcing provider taking charge of all IT
                    maintenance and business support. In contrast, co-sourced IT
                    support refers to an IT outsourcing provider supporting a
                    company’s in-house IT experts.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div className="col-md-3">
                <img src="/imgs/Group 1000002231.svg" />
              </div>
            </div>
            <div className="row">
              <div className="col-md-3 ">
                <img src="/imgs/Group 1000002250.svg" />
              </div>
              <div className="col-md-9">
                <div className="pl-90">
                  <h2>
                    Difference Between <br />
                    Outsourcing and Outstaffing
                  </h2>
                  <p>
                    Each of them includes the remote work, outstaffing stands
                    for hiring experienced professionals from other firms to
                    work on the project under control of the business owner and
                    outsourcing means passing the IT process to a third firm.
                  </p>

                  <p>
                    The service quality and the end product delivery in the
                    outsource are under the responsibility of outsourcing
                    provider, as well as any extra expenses while in the case of
                    outstaffing, the business owner takes responsibility on the
                    quality and the third party is only the resource provider.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div className="row">
              <div className="col-md-9">
                <div className="pr-90">
                  <h2>Why Outsourcing?</h2>
                  <p>
                    Did you know that most corporations use outsourcing to
                    insure their risks? <br />
                    Most of the big companies turn to more than one outsourcing
                    company to insure the risks and reach the best quality of IT
                    services. This has been a proven method in the industry for
                    many years, it is a good practice when the company uses only
                    40% in-house resources, and the remaining 60% is usually
                    distributed to two outsourcing companies. This model ensures
                    both security and decentralization as well as the best
                    quality because each party sees the competitor and tries to
                    show the best results.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div className="col-md-3">
                <img src="/imgs/Group 1000002234.svg" />
              </div>
            </div>

            <div className="row">
              <div className="col-md-3 ">
                <img src="/imgs/Group 1000002252.svg" />
              </div>
              <div className="col-md-9">
                <div className="pl-90">
                  <h2>How Can Outsourcing Help Your Business?</h2>
                  <p>
                    Regardless of the industry your business operates in,
                    technology is an essential element to the successful running
                    of an organisation. Maintaining an effective IT
                    infrastructure is vital, and an IT partner can enable you to
                    do this more efficiently. Outsourcing to an IT partner
                    provides you with access to specialist skills, resources and
                    processes that enhance IT performance that may not be
                    available in-house. There’s no wonder IT outsourcing is a
                    popular choice for many.
                    <br />
                    IT outsourcing is an opportunity, not a threat. Many
                    businesses choose to utilise an external provider as an
                    extension of an existing internal team.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
